Vue.js Lab: Product List with Cart
Objective

Practice Vue directives: v-if, v-else-if, v-else, v-show.

Work with different data types: string, number, boolean, array, object.

Learn event handling with @click.

Apply dynamic classes and data binding.

Requirements
                                                               1. Navbar

Create a responsive navbar using Bootstrap.

Display the cart count dynamically using {{ cartCount }}.

                                                               2. Data

Create a products array containing product objects with:

id → Number

name → String

price → Number

inStock → Boolean

Other data properties:

cartCount → Number (default 0)

showProducts → Boolean (default true)

discount → Number (e.g., 10)

                                                                3. Directives

v-if / v-else-if / v-else → show stock status:

Green text → In Stock

Yellow text → Limited Stock (price < 50)

Red text → Out of Stock

v-show → toggle the visibility of the product list.

                                                                 4. Event Handling

Use @click on the Add to Cart button to:

Increase cartCount by 1.

Show an alert with the product name added.

                                                             5. Dynamic Class

Grey out the product name if the product is out of stock.

6. Discount Message

Show a discount message only if discount > 0 using v-if.

7. Layout

Use Bootstrap grid to display products in 3 columns on larger screens.

Each product card should display:

Image

Name

Price

Stock status

Description

Add to Cart button
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8. Extra Challenge (Optional)

Calculate the total price of items in the cart.

Allow removing products from the cart dynamically.

Show a “No products available” message if the products array is empty.
